post_text: Due to a plumbing issue, CES will be closing early today, September 8, 2020. We ask that you please pick up your child as soon as possible. If someone other than you will be picking up your child please call us at 802-521-5600 to let us know. Bus transportation will run starting around 12:00- if your child is scheduled to ride the bus we will send them unless we hear otherwise. No child will be left at a bus stop without a family member. If you need to make changes to your child's afterschool arrangements please call us at 802-521-5600.

post_text: Let's hear it for our AMAZING Lamoille North nutrition team! They have served over 174,867 meals since the pandemic began! We are so very appreciative for the many months of hard work that they have done to keep our communities fed.
shared_text:
LNSD Nutrition & Farm to School
August 10 at 1:41 PM ¬∑

Dear Summer Nutrition Team,
On March 16th, we were called into action as essential workers to face the Covid -19 crisis that was closing our school buildings, businesses and economy.
Our mission was to make sure that the children in our community did not go hungry. YOU stepped up, YOU faced fear, YOU kept our kids fed and eased the anguish of Lamoille families.
We have kept the connection between school and home with nourishing meals and smiling eyes above our masks. We went above and beyond by continuing the fresh fruit and veggie program, handing out donations of produce and milk and checking in on some of our most vulnerable families.
I am honored to be a part of this team of professionals.

Thank you for giving up your vacation time and your summer days, for your dedication and passion for helping kids.
Please know how appreciated you are!
With all my respect and gratitude,
Karyl

post_text: Cambridge families! Please take a moment to fill out this brief survey about internet access.
shared_text:
LAMOILLE.TILSONTECH.COM
Lamoille Broadband Survey

Representative Lucy Rogers
August 5 at 7:34 PM ¬∑

Lamoille County folks: please fill out this quick (3 minute max) survey on Internet availability at your address. This survey is being conducted with funding from a Broadband Innovation Grant and will be used to help develop a plan for improving broadband infrastructure in underserved regions of Lamoille County. Please share with your friends and neighbors!

Six Lamoille County towns (Waterville, Cambridge, Johnson, Hyde Park, Morristown, and Eden, with Belvidere hopefully joining soon) banded together in July to form a brand new Communications Union District, called Lamoille FiberNet. The Communications Union District is a municipal entity that allows small towns to work together to build communications infrastructure and/or deliver broadband Internet to the people who live in the district. I am very excited about this development and will share more updates on Lamoille FiberNet in the future, but in the meantime please take a few minutes to fill out the survey! Thank you!
https://lamoille.tilsontech.com/

There has been a change of location for food distribution from the Vermont national Guard.
The Vermont National Guard will be at the Lamoille Union High School campus in Hyde Park on Friday, May 22, 2020, from 10:00 am to 2:00 pm distributing FEMA meal boxes along with produce, chicken and dairy products provided by the Abbey Group.
Everyone is welcome to come pick up food!

post_text: Earlier this week, 6th grade students celebrated the joys of winter with a tea and hot chocolate party with Mrs. Niedecker! Students either wrote or found short stories and poems and shared them with the others in the class. Students could choose between 5 types of tea and hot cocoa, as well as enjoy a small treat of chocolate chip cookies or croissants. Other adults who were free in the building stopped by briefly to listen to their stories, as well as a small group of first graders! What a delightful way to start off Wednesday!
